<HEAD>
<TITLE>Signet Security</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#008040" VLINK="#800040" ALINK="#804040">
<a href="http://www.signet.com/"><IMG SRC="images/logobchr.jpg" ALT="Signet Logo" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=38 BORDER=0></a>
<CENTER><a href="conindex.htm"><img src="images/xbtn_per.jpg" alt="Personal Finance Button"  border=0  height=89 width =100 ALIGN=ABSMIDDLE  ></a><FONT SIZE=+4><EM> Security</EM></FONT>
<a href="http://www.signet.com/"><img src="images/xbtn_hom.jpg" alt="Signet Homepage Button" border=0  height=89 width =100 ALIGN=ABSMIDDLE ></a><BR></CENTER>

<CENTER><img src="images/banr_bar.jpg" ></CENTER>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=+1>
Signet is currently developing and evaluating security measures to protect its customers' accounts.  Those measures include:
<UL>
<LI>RSA Encryption (SSL for example), which protects information transferred between customers and Signet.
<UL>
<LI>Netscape <A HREF="http://home.netscape.com/newsref/ref/internet-security.html">Internet Security</A>
</UL>

<LI>Firewall Technology, protecting unauthorized access to Signet's information systems.

<LI>User Name and Password requirements for accessing specific account information.
</UL>
While this is not a complete list, these are some of the security options Signet is actively pursuing in order to insure that each customer's account information and activity is kept confidential.

</FONT>
<P>
<CENTER><img src="images/banr_bar.jpg" ></CENTER>
