HTTP/1.0 200 OK
Server: Netscape-Communications/1.1
Date: Friday, 24-Jan-97 02:22:36 GMT
Last-modified: Wednesday, 22-Jan-97 15:54:36 GMT
Content-length: 6489
Content-type: text/html
</DOCHDR>
<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML//EN">
<HTML VERSION="2.0">
<HEAD>
<!-- WEBMAGIC VERSION NUMBER="2.0.1" -->
<!-- WEBMAGIC TRANSLATION NAME="ServerRoot" SRC="/var/www/htdocs/" DST="/" -->
<!-- WEBMAGIC TRANSLATION NAME="ProjectRoot" SRC="./" DST="" -->
<TITLE>Signet Small Business Employer and Employee Benefits</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY ALINK="#804040" VLINK="#800040" LINK="#008040" BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<CENTER><P ALIGN="CENTER"><A HREF="http://www.signet.com"><IMG SRC="/images/xbtn_hom.jpg" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="100" HEIGHT="89" BORDER="0" SGI_SETWIDTH SGI_SETHEIGHT SGI_FULLPATH="/var/www/htdocs/images/xbtn_hom.jpg"></A> <IMG SRC="/images/sfs_invguide.gif" ALIGN="RIGHT" WIDTH="117" HEIGHT="149" BORDER="0" SGI_SETWIDTH SGI_SETHEIGHT SGI_FULLPATH="/var/www/htdocs/images/sfs_invguide.gif"><FONT SIZE="6"> Employer and Employee Benefits</FONT>
<BR>(available through Signet Financial Services, Inc.)</CENTER><P><BR>
 </P>
<P><BR>

 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As businesses become more streamlined and more competitive, they hire the
most qualified employees, the ones who can deliver the most &quot;bang for the
buck&quot;. And they keep those employees by investing in employee benefit programs
which reflect the business' need for efficiency and effectiveness. How can
you compete with the big guys? You don't need to be a huge, multi-national
conglomerate to be able to offer a competitive benefits package to your
employees. You won't have to spend a lot to maintain your investment plan
when you choose Signet Bank's affiliate, Signet Financial Services, Inc. So you'll still have some
money left over to invest in your own retirement. And isn't that why you
work so hard in the first place? </P>
<P><A HREF="sbiz_retirementcalc.htm">Retirement Calculator</A> - How much will you need to save each month to reach your financial goal
by the time you retire? </P>
<P><A NAME="Investment/RetirementPlans">Investment/Retirement Plans</A> - </P>
<P><B><U>401 (k)</U></B> 
<UL>
<LI>Retirement savings plan which allows both employers and employees to contribute
tax-deferred savings to a retirement fund and select a range of investment
options 
<LI>Tax-deferral feature means that 100% of the amount contributed goes toward
the growth of employee retirement savings 
<LI>Low administrative costs, on-line record keeping, toll-free phone access
to plan data, and detailed monthly statements are a part of all 401
(k) plans available through Signet Financial Services, Inc.
<LI>401 (k) accounts offered through Kemper Funds, Fidelity
Investments, MFS Retirement Services, Inc., and The Principal Financial Group</UL>
<P><B><U>SIMPLE - Savings Incentive Match Plan for Employees</U></B> 
<UL>
<LI>Plan is designed for companies with less than 100 employees (replaces the
SARSEP [Salary Reduction Simplified Employee Pension] as of January 1, 1997) 
<LI>Can be set up as an IRA or a 401 (k) plan, but must be an employer's only
qualified retirement plan 
<LI>Maximum deferral is $6,000 
<LI>Required 2% employer contribution <U>or</U> a match of 100% up to 3% 
<LI>Plan is not subject to the special 401 (k) nondiscrimination rules or the
top-heavy rules 
</UL>
<P><B><U>SERP - Supplemental Executive Retirement Plans</U></B> 
<UL>
<LI>Non-qualified plan available only to C-Corporations 
<LI>Covers only a select group of highly compensated employees, allowing those
employees who typically &quot;max&quot; out of their 401 (k) plan to defer more income
for retirement 
<LI>No limit to employer contribution 
<LI>Enables pre-tax salary deferral and employer matching 
<LI>Employee deferral is limited to any reasonable amount up to 100% of salary
and/or bonuses 
</UL>
<P><B><U>SEP - Simplified Employee Pension</U></B> 
<UL>
<LI>Allows employers to contribute funds to individual employee accounts (typically
an Individual Retirement Account [IRA] created for the SEP) 
<LI>These funds are then tax-deductible for the employee 
<LI>Employee controls how the funds in his or her SEP are actually invested 
<LI>Earnings on funds are not taxed until the accumulated funds are distributed
at some future date (eligibility generally begins at age 59 1/2) 
</UL>

<P>*Mutual funds are sold by prospectus only.  A Signet Financial Services 
Investment Representative can supply them.  Please read them carefully before 
investing.
<P><CENTER>
Sorry, investments are not available through Signet Financial Services, Inc.
(member NASD) in Massachusetts.</CENTER></P>
<P><div align="center"><CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER=5 WIDTH=75% COLSPEC="L20">
<TR><TD>
<STRONG>Investment products are not deposits, obligations of, or guaranteed 
by any bank.  They are not insured by the FDIC.  They involve risk, including
the possible loss of principal invested.</STRONG>
</TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER></div></P>

<P>
