<HEAD><META name="GENERATOR" content="Mozilla/2.0GoldB1 (Win32)"><TITLE>Signet Bank Senior Officers</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#008040" VLINK="#800040" ALINK="#804040">
<CENTER>
<a href="http://www.signet.com/"><img src="images/xbtn_hom.jpg" alt="Signet Homepage Button" hspace=5 vspace=5 border=0  height=89 width =100 align=right ></a>
<BR>
<IMG SRC="images/banr_inf.jpg" ALT="Corporate Information Banner">

</CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="images/banr_bar.jpg"></CENTER>
	
<p><ALIGN=ABSMIDDLE><img src="images/logobchr.jpg"align=left><h1>Senior Management</h1></p>
<STRONG><font size=+1><p> Signet is governed by a group of senior executives who make strategic decisions collectively.  <br>
<p>
Management Committee</U></STRONG>
<ul>
<p>
<li><STRONG><EM>Malcolm S. McDonald<br> Chairman & Chief Executive Officer</EM>
<br>
</STRONG></li>Mac McDonald joined Signet in 1970 in the commercial banking unit and served in various executive capacities until being elected as president of Signet Banking Corporation in 1990. He received the additional responsibilities of chief operating officer in 1991.  McDonald is currently chairman of the Virginia Bankers Association and leads the Greater Richmond Chamber of Commerce.  He received his B.S. in business administration from the University of Minnesota.
<p>
<li><STRONG><EM>T. Gaylon Layfield III<br>
  President & Chief Operating Officer</EM></strong><br></li>Gaylon Layfield joined Signet in 1975 as an International Credit Analyst and was named to head the commercial line of business in 1987.  In 1991, he became officer-in-charge of the Consumer Banking division.  His current responsibilities include the branch delivery system, the brokerage and mutual fund subsidiaries, the trust company, the mortgage and installment loan businesses, the 24-hour Telephone Banking Center and the small business division.  Layfield holds an M.B.A. from the Colgate Darden School of Business at the University of Virginia and a B.A. in . in economics from the University of Virginia.
<p>
<li><STRONG><EM>Wallace B. Millner III<br>Vice Chairman & Chief Financial Officer </EM></STRONG></li><br>B. Millner joined Signet Banking Corporation in 1971 as director of trust investment research. Millner's current responsibilities include the Controller's Division and the Capital Markets group including funding, the bank's investment portfolios, foreign exchange, treasury and corporate finance.  He received his A.B. in economics from Davidson College and his M.B.A. in finance from the University of North Carolina.
<p>
<li>
<STRONG><EM>
Robert J. Merrick
<br>
Executive Vice President <br>
 Chief Credit Officer<br></strong></EM>
	Bob Merrick joined the former Bank of Virginia-Potomac in March 1976
 as vice president in charge of that affiliate's commercial lending effort. 
 He is a member of the Asset and Liability Committee and chairman of the Credit
 Policy Committee.
	Mr. Merrick received an A.B. degree in economics from Yale University
 and an M.S. degree in business finance from George Washington University.
<p>
</STRONG></EM>
</li>
<p>
<li><STRONG><EM>Kenneth H. Trout<br>Senior Executive Vice President<br>Commercial Banking</EM></STRONG><br></li>Ken Trout joined Signet Bank as an adjustor in the MasterCard Department in 1970 and has held various positions in Operations, Branch Banking and Commercial Lending. His current responsibilities include overseeing the Commercial Banking division of Signet Banking Corporation, including traditional commercial lending as well as cash management products, leasing, and innovative niche businesses. Trout received his B.S. in economics and business administration from Methodist College.
<p>
<li><STRONG><EM>Philip H. Davidson<br>Executive Vice President<br>Strategic Planning and Asset/Liability Committee</EM></STRONG><br></li>Philip Davidson joined the bank in 1974 as an economist.  He currently chairs the asset and liability committee and manages the corporation's strategic planning function.  Davidson received a B.A. in economics from the University of Michigan, an M.B.A. from Western Michigan University and a Ph.D. in Finance from the University of Illinois. He is co-author of <U>Banking Tomorrow, Managing Markets through Planning</U>, published in 1978.
<p>
<li><STRONG><EM>Sara R. Wilson <br>Executive Vice President <br>General Counsel</EM></STRONG></li><br>Sara Wilson began her career with Signet Banking Corporation in 1977 as a corporate attorney.  She is a graduate of Hamilton College with a B.A. in mathematics, and the T.C. Williams School of Law at the University of Richmond.  Wilson is active in the Virginia Bar Association and the American Bar Association as well as the Bankers Roundtable.  She is vice president of the American Bankers Associations Bank Counsel Unit and is a past chairperson of the Virginia Bankers Association's Legal Affairs Committee.<P>
<p>
</ul>
<STRONG><U>Senior Officers</U></STRONG>
<ul>
<p><li>David L. Brantley<br>Executive Vice President<br>Treasurer<br></li><p><li>W. H. Catlett Jr.<br>Executive Vice President<br>Controller<br></li><p><li>Keith A. Reynolds<br>Executive Vice President<br>General Auditor<br></li><p><li>H. Nathaniel Taylor<br>Executive Vice President <br>Human Resources Director<br></li><p>
