<html><head><title>Signet's Benefits</title></head> 

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#008040" VLINK="#800040" ALINK="#804040">

 <h1 align=center><img src="images/banr_emp.jpg" ALT="Signet Employment"><br>Employee Benefits</h1><h4 align=center>Signet offers a comprehensive compensation package, including a full range of employee benefits to regular, full time employees.  These employee benefits are constantly reviewed and may be modified or eliminated at any time to meet the changing needs of employees and the company.  Currently, these benefits, including a flexible benefits program, are as follows:</h4><ul><li><H3>Flexible Benefits</H3><blockquote>A flexible benefits program, Signet Choice, allows employees to select the benefits they need from a menu of options including:</blockquote><ul><li><H4>Medical and Dental Coverage</H4><blockquote>Signet offers a variety of managed care options as well as prescription drug and mental health and substance abuse benefits.</blockquote><li><H4>Employee Life Insurance</H4><blockquote>In addition to the core benefit provided by Signet, employees may purchase additional coverage.</blockquote><li><H4>Accidental Death and Dismemberment Insurance</H4>	<blockquote>This coverage pays benefits if you die or are seriously injured in an accident.</blockquote><LI><H4>Dependent Life Insurance</H4>	<blockquote>This benefit provides life insurance coverage for an employee's spouse and dependents.</blockquote><LI><H4>Health Care and Dependent Care Spending Accounts</H4>	<blockquote>Employees may use pre-tax dollars from their salaries to pay for medical/dental and or dependent care expenses.</blockquote><LI><H4>Vacation Buy/Sell</H4>       <blockquote>In addition to Signet's paid vacation, employees may buy or sell vacation days.</blockquote></ul><LI><H3>Other Employee Benefits</H3><blockquote>In addition to the flexible benefit options, Signet offers other benefits including:</blockquote><ul><LI><H4>Sick Pay</H4>	<blockquote>Signet provides sick pay benefits for personal and family illness.</blockquote><LI><H4>Short- and Long-term Disability</H4>	<blockquote>These plans provide coverage in the event of extended absence due to accident or illness.</blockquote><LI><H4>Paid Vacation</H4>	<blockquote>Paid vacation is provided based on the employee's position and length of service.</blockquote><LI><H4>Paid Holidays</H4>	<blockquote>Signet usually observes 10 paid holidays per year.</blockquote><LI><H4>Employee Savings Plan</H4> 	<blockquote>Employees may make pre- and post-tax contributions to this 401(k) savings plan.  Signet matches the first 6% of before-tax savings at 50 cents on the dollar and will make an extra 3% contribution of the participant's eligible base salary each year that Signet meets or exceeds the annual performance target. Employees direct the investment of their accounts among seven investment funds and may take advantage of loan and hardship withdrawal options.  The plan accepts rollovers from prior qualified retirement plans.</blockquote><LI><H4>Profit Sharing</H4><blockquote>	Profit Sharing is designed to encourage Signet employees to enhance the company's profitability and is paid in cash each year the company meets its performance target.</blockquote><LI><H4>Signet Retirement Account</H4>	<blockquote>Signet pays the full cost of this benefit which helps employees financially prepare for retirement.</blockquote><LI><H4>Stock Purchase Plan</H4>	<blockquote>Employees may purchase company stock at a discounted price.</blockquote><LI><H4>Employee Assistance Program</H4>	<blockquote>Employees and immediate family members may take advantage of personal and confidential counseling dealing with issues such as family, marital, financial, legal, emotional or substance abuse problems.</blockquote><LI><H4>Discounted Bank Services</H4>	<blockquote>Employees may be eligible for checking with no charge for monthly maintenance, special rates on bank cards and discounted rates on home mortgages and installment loans.</blockquote><LI><H4>Educational Assistance Program</H4>	<blockquote>Signet provides tuition assistance for pre-approved, work-related courses.</blockquote><LI><H4>Family and Medical Leave</H4>	<blockquote>Eligible employees may receive up to 12 weeks of unpaid, job protected leave for the birth of a child, placement of a child, serious health condition of employee, spouse, child or parent.</blockquote><LI><H4>Matching Gifts</H4>   <blockquote>  Signet matches certain employee contributions to eligible institutions, organizations, associations and funds.</blockquote></ul></ul>
<p>
