<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#008040" VLINK="#800040" ALINK="#804040">

 <h1 align=center><img src="images/banr_emp.jpg" ALT="Signet Employment"><br>College Recruiting</h1>
<br>
<br>
<IMG align=left height=150 width=125 SRC="images/crystal.gif">
<font size=+2>
<font size=+4>
B</font size><a href="ba2.html">usiness analysts</a> at Signet do not define themselves by their position on an organizational chart or the size of their office.  Our analysts distinguish themselves by the way they think, the  way they approach problems and the way they work together.  They blend strategic vision, persistent curiosity and a strong will to succeed.
<p>
<font size=+4>
A</font size>t Signet, we don't expect our analysts to conform to one image, with a particular major or career objective.  Instead, we seek prospects who demonstrate skill sets which we believe we can build upon and which will serve both employee and employer well in the future.  Our analysts are encouraged to articulate and work towards their personal goals.
<p>
<font size=+4>
W</font size>hen new graduates arrive at Signet, they are not placed in formal training programs or relegated to the back room to work on low-profile assignments.  From the first few days at Signet, business analysts are challenged to think strategically, develop leadership skills and work on implementation using <a href="ibdm.html">IBDM</a>.  New hires immediately become members of the project teams they join.
<p><center>
<img src="images/morris.gif"> 
</font>
<br>
<center><h3>
<a href="ba2.html">Apply Online, but first...</a></h3>
</center>
