<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Signet Bank</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#800000" ALINK="#FF0000">

<CENTER><TABLE>
<TR><TD><IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="images/logochr2.jpg"></TD><TD></TD><TD></TD><TD><FONT SIZE=+4 COLOR="#800000"><EM><B>Disbursement Services</B></EM></FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>

<BR><HR WIDTH=97% ALIGN=center SIZE=5>

<STRONG><FONT SIZE=+2>S</FONT>ignet Bank offers a wide array of disbursement services to fit your individual needs.  These services encompass unique offerings that provide benefits including disbursement processing, cash flow maximization, fraudulent disbursement minimization, and enhanced control over your payables.</STRONG>

<CENTER>
<TABLE CELLPADDING=5>
<TR VALIGN=MIDDLE>
<TD><IMG SRC="images/reddot.gif"> <STRONG><A HREF="#controlleddisburse">Controlled Disbursement Account</A></STRONG></TD>

<TD><IMG SRC="images/reddot.gif"> <STRONG><A HREF="#payabledraft">Payable Through Draft</A></STRONG></TD>

<TD><IMG SRC="images/reddot.gif"> <STRONG><A HREF="#positivepay">Positive Pay</A></STRONG>

</TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER>

<HR WIDTH=97% ALIGN=center SIZE=5>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+4 COLOR="#800000"><B><I>Integrated Payables Outsourcing</I></B></FONT></CENTER>

<BR><CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2 COLOR="#800000"><B>What It Does:</B></FONT></CENTER>

<STRONG>With a single electronic transmission, you can send us all of your ACH, EDI, wire transfer, and check payment instructions along with complete remittance information.  Signet does the rest, executing each payment instruction and delivering the remittance information according to your trading partners requirements.</STRONG><P>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2 COLOR="#800000"><B>Benefits of Integrated Payables Outsourcing:</B></FONT></CENTER>
<UL>
<STRONG><LI>Accepts payment instructions in many formats negating the need to be "EDI-capable".
<LI>Eliminates dual processes since you send the bank a single set of payment instructions for all payment types. 
<LI>Reduces the risk of check fraud since check stock is no longer maintained on-site.
<LI>Enables you to gain better control over the settlement process, leading to better cash forecasting and use of funds.
<LI>Allows cost reductions in staffing, postage, paper, and storage expense.
<LI>Strengthens trading partner relationships.
<LI>Provides the opportunity to streamline operations and increase efficiencies in the treasury and accounting areas of your company.
</STRONG></UL>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+4 COLOR="#800000"><B><I><A NAME="controlleddisburse">Controlled Disbursement Account</A></I></B></FONT></CENTER>

<BR><CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2 COLOR="#800000"><B>What it Does:</B></FONT></CENTER>

<STRONG>A Controlled Disbursement Account (CDA) is designed to give you exact, same-day clearing information on disbursed checks presented for payment.  Signet obtains the total amount of your daily clearings from the  Federal Reserve and provides this information to you allowing your company to receive a more accurate cash position.  Non-productive balances are eliminated and your ability to make investment or borrowing decisions on exact funding needs is enhanced. </STRONG><P>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2 COLOR="#800000"><B>Benefits of Controlled Disbursement:</B></FONT></CENTER>

<UL><STRONG><LI>Provides notification of check clearing totals by 10:00 a.m. each day via PC or touch-tone telephone.
<LI>Allows for same day funding of an account either from collected balances in another account via ZBA transfer or by wire transfer from another bank.
<LI>Produces a more accurate cash position eliminating non-productive balances.
<LI>Permits investment or borrowing decisions to be based on exact needs.
</STRONG></UL>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+4 COLOR="#800000"><B><I><A NAME="payabledraft">Payable Through Draft</A></I></B></FONT></CENTER>

<BR><CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2 COLOR="#800000"><B>What it Does:</B></FONT></CENTER>

<STRONG>A Payable Through Draft Account uses payment instruments that have the appearance of a check but are drawn directly on your company.  The Payable Through Draft gives your company two advantages.  First, you have the convenience of using a check-like instrument.  Second, you are better able to control frequent payments to field representatives while maintaining full control over your disbursements.</STRONG><P>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2 COLOR="#800000"><B>Benefits of a Payable Through Draft Account:</B></FONT></CENTER>

<UL><STRONG><LI>Allows field agents (such as insurance claim adjusters) to issue on-the-spot payments to your company's customers or vendors.
<LI> Gives your company full control over disbursements by enabling the review of draft payments before final payment.
</STRONG></UL>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+4 COLOR="#800000"><B><I><A NAME="positivepay">Positive Pay</A></I></B></FONT></CENTER>

<BR><CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2 COLOR="#800000"><B>What it Does:</B></FONT></CENTER>

<STRONG>Positive Pay helps your company track which checks have cleared your account and then manages the payment of these items. Checks may be automatically returned, or you can choose to send back only those items believed to be altered or fraudulent.  This service is most suited for high volume check customers that have centralized control of the check issuance function.  Check copies are not provided but if inspection is necessary, your company may want to consider the use of Signets Payable Through Draft service.</STRONG><P>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2 COLOR="#800000"><B>Benefits of Positive Pay:</B></FONT></CENTER>

<UL><STRONG><LI>Allows for enhanced control of company funds by providing daily information on individual checks that meet certain criteria.
<LI>Reduces the risk of losses as a result of fraud, forged and/or altered checks.  Checks presented but not recorded on company books will quickly alert management to potential risk.
</STRONG></UL>

<HR WIDTH=97% ALIGN=center SIZE=5>

<BR><CENTER><STRONG><A HREF="comm.htm"> Home</A> | <A HREF="account.htm"> Account Management</A> | <A HREF="ttax.htm"> TTax&#174</A> | <A HREF="payment.htm"> Electronic Payment</A> | <A HREF="lockbox.htm"> Lockbox</A> | <A HREF="image.htm"> Rapid Image</A> | <A HREF="form.htm"> Contact Us</A></STRONG></CENTER><BR>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="images/banr_bar.jpg"></CENTER><P>
