<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Signet Bank Other Links</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#800000" ALINK="#FF0000">
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+3 COLOR="#800000"><B>Let Signet Residential Construction do the searching for you.  Check out these information packed sites.</B></FONT></CENTER>

<UL>
<FONT SIZE=+2><B><LI><A HREF="#reconstruction">Real Estate & Construction Trends</A>
<LI><A HREF="#employment">Employment Outlook</A>
<LI><A HREF="#demographics">Demographics... What Does Today's Homebuyer Look Like?</A>
<LI><A HREF="#competition">Checking Out the Competition... What Are Other Builders Doing?</A>
<LI><A HREF="#permits">Housing Permits, Houses Sold, and Economic Indicators</A>
<LI><A HREF="#personal">Personal Finance, News, Sports, Weather and More!</A></B></FONT>
</UL>

<HR WIDTH=97% ALIGN=center SIZE=5>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+3 COLOR="#800000"><B><A NAME="reconstruction">Real Estate and Construction Trends</A></B></FONT></CENTER>

<UL>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B><LI>Did you know that the <A HREF="http://www.nahb.com/nhp.html">Quality Adjusted Median New Home Price</A> increased 140% between 1978 and 1995?

<LI>See how the <A HREF="http://www.nahb.com/sf.html">Characteristics of New Single Family Homes</A> and <A HREF="http://www.nahb.com/sneh.html">Sales of New and Existing Homes</A> have changed over time.

<LI>Check out the <A HREF="http://www.fdic.gov/research/retrends/1996oct/index.html">FDIC Survey of Real Estate Trends</A>, a quarterly report of trends observed by managers at federal bank and thrift regulatory agencies.  

<LI>For more housing trends visit: <A HREF="http://www.aia.org/pubaffs/forecast.htm">AIA (American Institute of Architects) Residential Housing Market Forecasts</A> and <A HREF="http://www.nahb.com/starts.html">NAHB's Single Family and Multi-Family Housing Starts 1978-1995.</A></B></FONT>
</UL>


<HR WIDTH=97% ALIGN=center SIZE=5>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+3 COLOR="#800000"><B><A NAME="employment">Employment Outlook</A></B></FONT></CENTER>

<UL>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B><LI>Employment or Interest Rates - Which Affects the Housing Market More?  See <A HREF="http://www.builderonline.com/builder/monthly/jan96/aff196.htm">Employment:  The True Affordability Barometer</A> in BuilderOnline for one opinion.

<LI>Visit these sites for <A HREF="http://stats.bls.gov:80/cgi-bin/surveymost?la">State and Local Unemployment Statistics</A> and <A HREF="http://stats.bls.gov:80/cgi-bin/surveymost?gp">State and Local Unemployment Statistics by Demographic Profile</A>.  At these sites select the state you are interested in and then choose the tables you want to see.  For example, after choosing Maryland, statistics for the entire state or Baltimore can be selected.

<LI>North Carolina builders should visit the <A HREF="http://www.esc.state.nc.us/lmi/index.html">Employment Security Commission - Labor Market Information Division</A>.  This site provides employment information by county and information on the Tarheel state's largest employers.  Who are the top two employers in North Carolina's manufacturing sector?  Visit this site to find out.  </B></FONT>
</UL>

<HR WIDTH=97% ALIGN=center SIZE=5>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+3 COLOR="#800000"><B><A NAME="demographics"></A>Demographics...What Does Today's Home Buyer Look Like?</B></FONT></CENTER>

<UL>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B><LI>Find out your state's population and population growth patterns by visiting the <A HREF="http://www.census.gov/population/pop-profile/sttrend.html">Census Bureau's State Population Trends</A> page or its <A HREF="http://www.census.gov/population/pop-profile/stproj.html">State Population Projection</A> page.  

<LI>How are Baby Boomers changing the housing market?  Check out <A HREF="http://www.builderonline.com/builder/monthly/jan96/dem196.htm">BuilderOnline's Buyer Demographics</A>.  For information on the age distribution across the nation see <A HREF="http://www.nahb.com/trend1.html">Age Structure</A>.</B></FONT>
</UL>

<HR WIDTH=97% ALIGN=center SIZE=5>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+3 COLOR="#800000"><B><A NAME="competition"></A>Checking Out the Competition...What are Other Builders Doing?</B></FONT></CENTER>

<UL>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B><LI>Wondering where other builders are building and what their new homes look like?  Find out by browsing the <A HREF="http://www.texasweb.com/a/#top">Accurate New Home Builder Web Guide</A> which provides an index of home builders by state who are advertising their homes on the Web.  A growing number of builders have floor plans, photos of completed homes, and maps on their web sites. 

<LI>If you operate in the Greater Charlotte Area, Triad Piedmont, or Research Triangle areas of North Carolina go to <A HREF="http://www.bpls.com/">The Builder's Profile and Listing System</A> to see what's happening in your neck of the woods.  

<LI>Talking to your local Builders Association can give you valuable information and contacts in your community.  For a list of associations in your state, go to <A HREF="http://www.nahb.com/slass.html">NAHB's State and Local Builders Associations Page</A>.</B></FONT>
</UL>

<HR WIDTH=97% ALIGN=center SIZE=5>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+3 COLOR="#800000"><B><A NAME="permits"></A>Housing Permits, Homes Sold, and Economic Indicators</B></FONT></CENTER>

<UL>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B><LI>To see the value (in $000s) of August 1996 Housing Permits in your MSA visit the <A HREF="http://www.census.gov/const/C40/Permits_by_MSA/tb3v9608.txt">Census Bureau's New Privately Owned Housing Units Authorized Valuation by Metro Area</A> and for the number of units in your MSA visit <A HREF="http://www.census.gov/const/C40/Permits_by_MSA/tb3u9608.txt">New Privately Owned Housing Units Authorized Unadjusted Units by Metro Area</A>.  These sites give data for single family permits and multi unit permits.

<LI>Check out the <A HREF="http://www.rfa.com/Free.stm">Free Lunch</A> section of the RFA's home page to get leading economic indicators by state and find out how the cost of doing business in your state compares to the rest of the nation.

<LI>For regional data on the <A HREF="http://www.census.gov/const/c25_curr.txt">Number of Single Family Homes Sold</A>, go to this Census Bureau link.</B></FONT>
</UL>

<HR WIDTH=97% ALIGN=center SIZE=5>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+3 COLOR="#800000"><B><A NAME="personal"></A>Personal Finance, News, Sports, Weather and More!</B></FONT></CENTER>

<UL>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B><LI>Need tips on how to invest and manage your hard earned dollars?  Visit <A HREF="http://kiplinger.com/magazine/maghome.html">Kiplinger's Personal Finance Magazine</A>.  To help you keep track of what the stock markets are doing, visit <A HREF="http://www.cnbc.com/">CNBC</A> and <A HREF="http://www.cnnfn.com/">CNNfn</A>.  For stock quotes that are delayed only 20 minutes behind market, visit <A HREF="http://www.dbc.com/">DBC Online</A> to see how the stocks in your portfolio are doing.

<LI>How's the weather?  <A HREF="http://the-tech.mit.edu/Weather/">The Lighthouse On-Line</A> weather information can give you up to date forecasts for your hometown or for anywhere you may be traveling.  

<LI>For breaking news visit <A HREF="http://www.cnn.com/">CNN's Home Page</A> and <A HREF="http://www2.nando.net/nt/nando.cgi">The Nando Times</A>.  For a mix of news and entertainment visit <A HREF="http://www.pathfinder.com">Pathfinder</A>. 

<LI>To help you find what you are looking for on and off the Web, check out <A HREF="http://www.the-yellowpages.com">The Internet Yellow Pages</A> and <A HREF="http://www.iguide.com/insites/index.sml">iGuide Net Reviews</A>.  

<LI>Golfers:  Did you know that you can now set your tee times online?  Visit the <A HREF="http://www.usgolfcourses.com">U.S. Golf Courses</A> site to find out how.  Stop by the <A HREF="http://www.enews.com/magazines/golf/">South Carolina Golf Guide</A> and the <A HREF="http://www.sccsi.com/sc/golf/scgolf.html">South Carolina Official Golf Guide</A> for golf tips from leading pros, a quiz to test your knowledge of the sport and much more.</B></FONT>

</UL>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=2>Signet provides links to other sites as a service to our customers and is not associated wih linked sites nor responsible for the accuracy, completeness,
or content of material on linked sites.</FONT></CENTER>



