<HTML> 
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Investor Profiler</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#008040" VLINK="#800040" ALINK="#804040">
<a href="http://www.signet.com"><IMG SRC="images/logobchr.jpg" ALT="Signet Logo" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=38 BORDER=0></a>
<CENTER><a href="http://www.signet.com/perfinance/conindex.htm"><img src="images/xbtn_per.jpg" alt="Personal Finance Button"  border=0  height=89 width =100 ALIGN=left ></a>
<a href="http://www.signet.com"><img src="images/xbtn_hom.jpg" alt="Signet Homepage Button" border=0  height=89 width =100 ALIGN=right ></a>
<FONT SIZE=+3><EM> Investor Profile Worksheet</EM></FONT>
<P>
<font size=+2><em>Available from Signet Financial Services, Inc.</font>
<font size=+1><sup>*</sup></font></em>

</CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><img src="images/banr_bar.jpg" ></CENTER><P>
<FONT SIZE=+1><EM><CENTER>Understanding your goals and expectations is the first step to take toward achieving them.  The questions that follow will help develop an accurate financial picture of your life -- and to get a good idea of where you want to be in the future.  The answers you choose will indicate your comfort level with investment risk -- and your ability to withstand it.  You'll analyze your day-to-day financial needs, your general investment style, and your personal time horizon.
<P>
</CENTER></EM>
<P>
<CENTER>Answer the following questions honestly and accurately, then submit the worksheet to receive your asset allocation profile from Signet Financial Services, Inc., online, in seconds..</CENTER>
<P>
</FONT>
<CENTER><img src="images/banr_bar.jpg" ></CENTER>

<FORM METHOD=POST ACTION="/cgi-bin/sfs_imprint.pl">

<B>1.  Which factor is most important before choosing an investment?</B>
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="factor" VALUE="15">How quickly I will be able to increase my wealth.
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="factor" VALUE="9">The amount of monthly income the investment will generate.
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="factor" VALUE="3">The safety of my investment principal.
<P>
<BR><B>2.  Which of the following statements best describes your approach to investing?</B>
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="approach" VALUE="3">Forego capital gains ensuring there is little risk to principal.
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="approach" VALUE="6">To increase investment value with minimal potential for loss.
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="approach" VALUE="9">To pursue investment growth, accepting moderate levels of risk and principal fluctuation.
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="approach" VALUE="15">To maximize long-term returns, accepting maximum risk of principal fluctuation.
<P>
<BR><B>3.  If a $10,000 investment that you made for ten years lost value during the first year, at what point would you sell and move to a more stable investment, rather than wait for a turnaround?</B>
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="hyploss" VALUE="3">$9,500
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="hyploss" VALUE="6">$9,000 to $9,499
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="hyploss" VALUE="9">$8,000 to $8,999
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="hyploss" VALUE="15">Less than $8,000
<P>
<CENTER><img src="images/banr_bar.jpg" ></CENTER>
<BR><B>4.  In general, my attitude about the U.S. and the world economics is:</B>
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="macecon" VALUE="1">Pessimistic
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="macecon" VALUE="2">Unsure
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="macecon" VALUE="3">Optimistic
<P>
<BR><B>5.  In about how many years do you expect to need the money you are investing?</B>
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="length" VALUE="1">Within 2 to 3 years
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="length" VALUE="3">Within 4 to 5 years
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="length" VALUE="5">Within 6 to 10 years
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="length" VALUE="8">More than 10 years
<P>
<BR><B>6.  When will 20% of your portfolio be withdrawn for short-term financial needs?</B>
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="shorterm" VALUE="5">More than 7 years
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="shorterm" VALUE="3">Within 3 to 7 years
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="shorterm" VALUE="1">Less than 3 years
<P>
<CENTER><img src="images/banr_bar.jpg" ></CENTER>
<BR><B>7.  What is your current age?</B>
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="age" VALUE="25">Under 30
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="age" VALUE="16">Between 30 to 45
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="age" VALUE="9">Between 46 to 55
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="age" VALUE="4">Between 56 to 62
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="age" VALUE="1">Over 62
<P>
<BR><B>8.  Which statement best describes your income needs?</B>
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="needs" VALUE="5">I can forego at least 10% of my current income
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="needs" VALUE="3">My present income is adequate for my needs
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="needs" VALUE="1">I need at least 10% more income
<P>
<CENTER><img src="images/banr_bar.jpg" ></CENTER>
<BR><B>9.  How would you use the earnings of your investment portfolio?</B>
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="usage" VALUE="7">Reinvest 100% of my investment earnings
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="usage" VALUE="5">Reinvest 80 to 100% of my investment earnings
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="usage" VALUE="3">Reinvest 20 to 79% of my investment earnings
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="usage" VALUE="1">Reinvest 0% (Receive all investment earnings as income.)
<P>
<BR><B>10.  What is the current value of your investment portfolio?</B>
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="value" VALUE="5">More than $500,000
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="value" VALUE="4">$100,000 to $500,000
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="value" VALUE="3">$50,000 to $99,999
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="value" VALUE="2">$25,000 to $49,999
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="value" VALUE="1">Less than $25,000
<P>
<BR><B>11.  How many months of living expenses could be safely covered by your current liquid investments?</B>
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="emergenc" VALUE="5">More than 12 months
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="emergenc" VALUE="3">Between 4 and 12 months
<BR><INPUT TYPE="RADIO" NAME="emergenc" VALUE="1">Less than 4 months
<P>
