<HEAD>
<TITLE>Chapter 1</TITLE>
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1"></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" LINK="#008040" VLINK="#800040"><!-- Chapter 1
(ch1.html) -->
<P><A HREF="toc1.html"><IMG
SRC="../images/artb_bk.jpg" ALT="Book Icon" ALIGN="left" BORDER="0" HSPACE="0" WIDTH="100" HEIGHT="89"></A>
<A HREF="index.html"><IMG
SRC="../images/xbtn_edu.jpg" ALT="Educational Funding Button" ALIGN="right" BORDER="0" HSPACE="0" WIDTH="100" HEIGHT="89"></A></P>
<P ALIGN="center"><FONT SIZE="6"><B>Chapter 1</B></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="center"><FONT SIZE="4"><B>Using this Guide</B></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="center">Visit our <A HREF="bkorder.html"><B>Bookstore</B> </A>to
order your copy of <I>Don't Miss Out</I> <BR> and other College Financing
Guides. <BR>
</P>
<P><A HREF="toc1.html">Table of Contents</A><BR>
</P>
<P ALIGN="center"><IMG
SRC="../images/banr_bar.jpg" ALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="474" HEIGHT="15"> </P>
<P><FONT SIZE="4"><STRONG>Organization Of Guide</STRONG></FONT><BR> The
sequence of topics at this site parallels the steps you should take in your
quest to finance  college. First, you must define your monetary need and second,
you must learn how to finance that  need. Please don't skip to the scholarship
resource sections and begin firing off appeals for help. </P>
<P>For most people, equating the financial aid process with an isolated search
for scholarships is an  unproductive way to spend time, and the time of the kind
organizations offering assistance. Instead,  start at the beginning.<BR>
</P>
<P>First you will explore the larger trends in higher education finance, as
well as learn to separate fact  from fiction.<BR>
</P>
<P>Then you will learn the special vocabulary of financial aid. You will meet
the players in the financial  aid game, and you will learn how to calculate your
family contribution-the amount of money your  family will be judged capable of
contributing to college costs. We will guide you through the entire  aid
application process and show you how to take charge of each step along the way.</P>
<P><BR>
<STRONG>Why is taking charge important?</STRONG><BR> 1.	It increases your
eligibility for aid.<BR> 2.	It enhances your chances of receiving all the aid
to which you are entitled.<BR> 3.	It improves the composition of your
award-more grants and fewer loans.<BR>
</P>
<P>Third, you move from fundamentals to more advanced topics. You become a
master of the financial  aid game-college selection, personal finance and tax
strategies. You learn the best moves for two  different situations: when college
entrance is approaching fast and when college is still years away.<BR>
</P>
<P>Fourth, you will meet the major money sources-the colleges, Uncle Sam, and
the states. They are  the dispensers of billions of dollars. By getting to know
their programs well, you will not overlook a  single penny that is due you.<BR>
</P>
<P>Fifth, you learn about two major alternatives for financing college
costs-your boss, and the US  military. The suggestions may not be to your
liking, but you should know about them and consider  or reject them at this
point in the process.<BR>
</P>
<P>And finally, you get to special opportunities. You've already had the meat
and potatoes course.  Now you are looking for the cake or maybe just the
frosting. You'll find sections here for the bright,  the career-oriented, the
athlete, the graduate student, and for minorities and women. <BR>
<I>Don't Miss Out</I> concludes with tips to bring together many of the ideas
developed earlier at greater  length. Use these tips as a review. </P>
<P ALIGN="center"><IMG
SRC="../images/banr_bar.jpg" ALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="474" HEIGHT="15"> </P>
<P><IMG
SRC="../images/artb_lpt.jpg" ALT="Laptop Computer" ALIGN="left" HSPACE="0" WIDTH="100" HEIGHT="89">
<IMG
SRC="../images/artb_cu2.jpg" ALT="Laptop Computer" ALIGN="right" HSPACE="0" WIDTH="100" HEIGHT="89">
</P>
<P ALIGN="center"><A HREF="toc1.html">Table of Contents</A><BR>
